message.entry: Expected ObjectAttributes to be a struct.\nIf this track is an output of a tracker, use detections with ObjectAttributes defined as a struct.
In code generation, {0} can only be set on construction.
The value assigned to {0} must be ''History'', ''Score'', or ''Integrated''.
Expected {0} to be a vector of probabilities.\nAll entries must be positive, less than or equal to 1, and sum to 1.
When {0} is set to a non scalar value, {1} must correspond to the linear index into {0} that corresponds to the maximum probability.
Input argument {0,number,integer} needs to be either an array of objectTrack objects, a struct array of equivalent structures, or a state parameter struct array.
